{
  "stem": "1965.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I carried it until this time, at this present.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I'm very much concerned continuously with the welfare of children, specifically because children is the future.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They are the hope and the inspiration of continuation of life.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And children need to be loved, disciplined, and respected.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I don't see it too much today, unfortunately.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Children have gone into-- for that matter, the way I see right now, what is happening to children, is that children almost have to go into hiding places.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Where I used to hide to survive from a Holocaust-- I see today, in our cities of the United States, that children almost have to go in hiding, so they should not get molested or killed.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "This is a very, very sad day to discover that something like that goes on in the finest country in the world.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My mother and father were second cousins.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My father was born and raised in Krosno, Poland.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And my mother was raised and born in Bremen, Germany.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But their heritage, on my mother's side, was first born and raised in Poland.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They migrated to Germany, and that's where my mother was born.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I am also proud to say that I am-- how we should we say that?",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My forefather was the man who was born in 1707.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I discovered that two years ago-- who has a book known as [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he was a mystical rabbi in Poland, and he wrote about life and living.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It is this book up to today that is reverent in the Hasidic world.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And my late grandfather, the only one who was really able to survive the Holocaust, but died an early death in New York City, he came here because people wanted him here-- Yehoshua Wagschal-- Rabbi Yehoshua Wagschal.",
      "word_count": 37
    }
  ],
